title: Baby Dream Kardashian is the spitting image of dad Rob Kardashian in brand new video
text:

Baby Dream Kardashian may only be three months old, but she's already establishing herself as part of the most famous reality TV family ever. 
The little girl, who was born on November 10 2016, looks more like her dad Rob Kardashian every day, as evidenced in the most recent Snapchats shared by mum Blac Chyna. 
In the cute footage, Chyna coos at her daughter and Dream smiles and laughs as she lays on her back. Read More Dream looks more like Rob every day (Photo: SnapChat/blacchynala) Chyna and Rob in New York, January 17th 2017 (Photo: Splash News) 
Wearing a grey top and a white bib, Dream responds to her mum's facial expressions and smiles as Chyna tickles her mouth with the teat of her milk bottle. 
There's no denying her family resemblance to Rob, as even he had shared a side-by-side comparison of himself as a young boy next to his daughter on Instagram earlier this week. https://www.instagram.com/p/BPwUxe-gOcX/embed 
In the Snapchat video, Chyna can be seen wearing her giant diamond engagement ring from Rob, hinting that the new parents are still very much together. 
It comes after the couple, who have been dating for a year, had a very public split shortly after the birth of their daughter. Dream responds to Blac Chyna's cooing (Photo: SnapChat/blacchynala) The baby smiled as her mum played with her (Photo: SnapChat/blacchynala) 
After a string of messages were posted to Chyna's Instagram account - which she said had been hacked - Rob showed his Snapchat followers his bare house as it emerged Chyna had moved out, and taken everything with her. 
However, fans were cynical about the timing of their fight, given that it came just a couple of days before the launch of their new E! reality show, Rob & Chyna. 
Since then the two have patched things up, and Rob is still posting clips and pictures of his fiancee on his social media. 
But Chyna hasn't reciprocated in kind - she even shared snaps from a recent family portrait with both Dream and her older son King Cairo that didn't include Rob at all. Read More
